title._content: Happy Young Woman with a Bumper Sticker Which Reports She Had Successfully Passed Testing at an Auto Emission Inspection Station in Downtown Cincinnati, Ohio...09/1975

description._content: Original Caption: Happy Young Woman with a Bumper Sticker Which Reports She Had Successfully Passed Testing at an Auto Emission Inspection Station in Downtown Cincinnati, Ohio. Her First Test Was Unsuccessful, and She Had to Return after Her Auto's Carburetor Was Adjusted at a Service Station. Emissions Testing for Carbon Monoxide and Hydrocarbons Has Been in Effect Since January, 1975 All Vehicles in the City Must Pass a Safety Check. 09/1975 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-15478 Photographer: Eiler, Lyntha Scott, 1946- Subjects: Cincinnati (Hamilton county, Ohio, United States) inhabited place Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: arcweb.archives.gov/arc/action/ExternalIdSearch?id=557928 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
